# Security and privacy

- Do: redact secrets from Debug/Display; use OS CSPRNG; constant-time compare for tokens.
- Do: classify every network field (purpose, owner, retention, deletion).
- Do: strip EXIF/GPS from shared media; keep precise location in memory only.
- Do: bound all parsers (size, depth, decode time, dimensions).
- Never: custom cryptographic primitives; log PII, profile text, messages, exact location, or evidence.
- Never: force-unwrap/panic in normal mobile or service control flow.
- Never: disable TLS validation in release builds.
- Verify: `make security` and relevant unit tests for touched modules.
